      BEGIN DSSUBRECORD
         Name "REJCDE1"
         Description =+=+=+=
The first code sent to the provider indicating the reason for adjustment or reject. Examples:  
?? (?M/I? MEANS MISSING/INVALID)  
?1 M/I BIN 
?2 M/I VERSION NUMBER  
?3 M/I TRANSACTION CODE  
?4 M/I PROCESSOR CONTROL NUMBER  
?5 M/I PHARMACY NUMBER  
?6 M/I GROUP NUMBER  
?7 M/I CARDHOLDER ID NUMBER  
?8 M/I PERSON CODE  
A total list of reject codes can be created by querying the RxTRACK? reference file RTRCP (conflict codes).
